"A standard pour yields two plus fingers worth of rich voluminous crisp medium khaki colored frothy goodness...  Really good retention...  The color is a medium to dark brown with just a touch or murkiness mixed in...  A moderate bit of moderate paced carbonation...  The aroma is rich with sweet potato, marshmallow and toffee...  A hint of milk chocolate and brown sugar as well...  Very pleasant aroma all the way around...  The flavor is rich and robust but a significant deviation from the aroma...  Roasted malt, coffee and peat materialize after not being detected on the nose...  There is actually a fairly potent hop bite, especially by style standards...  The end result is a highly complex and highly enjoyable flavor profile...  The mouthfeel is a tad bit thin and on the lighter side of medium bodied...  Crisp with some prickly carbonation...  A rather enjoyable beer...  This style seems to be falling a bit out of mainstream, but it is one that I still greatly...  It's brews like this that remind what an exquisite style it really is..."
