"The beer pours a bubbly slightly tannish head that dissipates very quickly. The beer itself is a clear and brown copper. The beer smell has strong sweet and caramel notes with a bit of the sweet potato. The sweet potato is fairly distinct from the other notes. The hops are barely noticeable but give off a floral aroma. The taste has the same notes but at different strengths. The hops are slightly stronger and the sweet potato is more noticeable and stands apart from the rest of the beer. The malt and caramel notes are not as strong as they were in the smell and are covered by the sweet potato. The change is not bad but could have been better incorporated even though it still works. The mouthfeel is a bit heavy bodied and thick but light enough to be smooth with the biting carbonation. Overall, a decent beer and okay."
