"12 ounce bottle into snifter, bottled on 6/4/2014. Pours lightly cloudy deep ruby/brown color with a 1 finger dense light khaki head with good retention, that reduces to a small cap that lingers. Nice soapy lacing clings on the glass, with a good amount of streaming carbonation. Aromas of caramel, toast, brown sugar, raisin, brown bread, herbal, grass, light roast, light nuttiness, and yeast earthiness. Nice and pleasant aromas with good complexity and balance of dark/bready malt, earthy hop, and yeast ester notes; with solid strength. Taste of caramel, toast, brown sugar, brown bread, raisin, plum, herbal, grass, light roast, light nuttiness, and yeast earthiness. Fair amount of earthy herbal bitterness on the finish; with lingering notes of caramel, toast, brown sugar, brown bread, raisin, plum, herbal, grass, light roast, and yeast earthiness on the finish for a good bit. Nice complexity and balance of dark/bready malt, earthy hops, and yeast ester flavors; with a good malt/bitterness balance and zero cloying flavors after the finish. Medium carbonation and body; with a smooth and fairly creamy/bready mouthfeel that is nice. Alcohol is well hidden with minimal warming present after the finish. Overall this is a nice and unique scottish ale. Good complexity and balance of dark/bready malt, earthy hops, and yeast ester flavors; and very smooth to drink. A nicely enjoyable offering."
